article.description: Billy Giles scored 23 points with 10 rebounds, Isaiah Still added 22 and Robert Morris cruised past Bryant 89-71 on Saturday.
article.headline: Robert Morris cruises past Bryant 89-71
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, N.J. -- Billy Giles scored 23 points with 10 rebounds, Isaiah Still added 22 and Robert Morris cruised past Bryant 89-71 on Saturday. The Colonials (7-18, 5-7 Northeast) shot 55 percent from the field despite going 4 of 15 from beyond the arc. They dominated the boards, 42-27, led by Rodney Pryor's 11. Pryor added 14 points on 5-of-9 shooting. Bryant (7-18, 4-8) was led by Nisre Zouzoua with 17 points. Curtis Oakley had 16 points and Marcel Pettway added 11. The Bulldogs led early, but Robert Morris made a 14-3 run midway through the first half and led 44-37 at the break. The lead grew to 17 after an eight-point spurt early in the second half, as Giles threw down a dunk and followed with a putback of his own miss on the next possession.
